Here are both approaches:

**1. Passing a simple string (product ID):**

```csharp
// ProductListPage.xaml.cs or ViewModel
async void OnProductSelected(Product product)
{
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"ProductDetailsPage?productId={product.Id}");
}
```

**2. Passing the full object via a dictionary:**

```csharp
async void OnProductSelected(Product product)
{
    var navParams = new Dictionary<string, object>
    {
        { "product", product }
    };
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("ProductDetailsPage", navParams);
}
```

**Receiving both on the ViewModel with `IQueryAttributable`:**

```csharp
public class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach 1: simple string parameter
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var idObj))
        {
            string productId = idObj.ToString();
            // fetch product from service, etc.
            LoadProduct(productId);
        }

        // Approach 2: full object (passed via dictionary overload)
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var productObj) && productObj is Product product)
        {
            Name = product.Name;
            Price = product.Price;
            // use directly — no extra fetch needed
        }
    }
}
```

**Wire the ViewModel to the page:**

```csharp
// ProductDetailsPage.xaml.cs
public ProductDetailsPage(ProductDetailsViewModel vm)
{
    InitializeComponent();
    BindingContext = vm;
}
```

**Register the route and DI:**

```csharp
// MauiProgram.cs / AppShell
Routing.RegisterRoute("ProductDetailsPage", typeof(ProductDetailsPage));

// MauiProgram.cs
builder.Services.AddTransient<ProductDetailsPage>();
builder.Services.AddTransient<ProductDetailsViewModel>();
```

**Key differences:**

| | String param | Object param |
|---|---|---|
| Method | `GoToAsync(uri)` | `GoToAsync(uri, dict)` |
| Received as | `object` → call `.ToString()` | `object` → cast to `Product` |
| Use case | Deep links, simple IDs | In-app nav with rich data |
| URI-safe | ✅ Yes | ❌ Not serialized to URI |

The `IQueryAttributable` interface gives you a single `ApplyQueryAttributes` entry point that handles both cases — Shell calls it automatically when the page resolves your ViewModel as its `BindingContext`.
